modules.description: Encodes binary data to ASCII85 format using Adobe's specification, handling padding and special cases. Processes byte sequences and provides a command-line interface for file encoding. Accepts input from files or standard input and outputs encoded strings to standard output.

Encodes binary data into ASCII85 format, reading from a string header and input channel, then writing the encoded result to an output channel. Processes byte streams directly, handling end-of-input automatically. Useful for embedding binary content in text-based formats, such as generating ASCII85-encoded PostScript data.
